18/01/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- UN war crimes tribunal investigators questioned former assistant Interior Minister Josko Moric in Zagreb on Saturday (17 January), according to the Croatian national television HTV.
As in the recent case of another ex-top police official, Zdravko Janic, Moric was reportedly interviewed in relation to the Medak Pocket operation of 1993 and the 1995 Storm operation, with particular emphasis on the role of the Croatian police.
According to HTV, the interviews with former defence and police officials should be completed by the start of next month.
(HINA, BBC - 17/01/04)
